Aiming at a further rationalize the starch influence on the material and device performances, we investigated the optical properties of the films. In perovskite materials, a range of different charge-carrier recombination mechanisms occur, which depend on the charge-carrier density (n) to a different degree. The rate of change in n can be expressed through the following equation (1):1dn(t)dt=−nk1−n2k2−n3k3\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
